<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-08T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-08T13:00:00-05:00" n="827" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d827">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./1036: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-08T15:00:00-03:00">May 8,
                                    1940—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 8—2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>196. Buenos Aires telegram No. 127, May 7, 6 p.m. Aranha tells me that he
                            has taken no action and is awaiting a reply to my telegram No. 189, May
                            1, 2 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>